text: They change owners now selling nasi lemak also... quite affordable.

This stall serves local comfort food like fried bee hoon & noodles, chee chiong fun and peanut porridge.

It also sells an assortment of add-ons like luncheon meat, fish cake, fish fillet and very runny sunny side up.

The chee chiong fun is silky smooth and is a hot favourite among diners here.

The stall opens early in the morning at 6am and usually sells out by lunch time.

Do note that the stall is closed very Thursday.
Delicious breakfast bee hoon and chi chon fun. It’s long queue, but quite fast you can get your food…👍👍🇸🇬🇸🇬😀😀
Yummy breakfast option with affordable food!  Bee Hoon + Noodle + Fried Fish Cutlet cost $2.20.  Hard to find such economy food already.
